      "id": "ev:economics-relay-unattributed-suppression-coverage-gap-fail-open-direction-untested.flow-agents-workflow.coverage-gap-not-an-ac-failure-fault-injecting-the-fail-open-guard-itself-reverting-if-jq-rc-eq-0-has-signal-false-to-if-has-signal-true-which-changes-behavior-only-when-the-internal-jq-call-fails-returns-non-true-false-was-not-caught-by-evals-integration-test-economics-record-sh-the-suite-still-reported-all-checks-passed-after-this-mutation-root-cause-the-suite-has-no-black-box-way-to-force-the-guard-s-internal-jq-call-to-fail-because-record-is-always-well-formed-json-assembled-by-the-emitter-s-own-earlier-jq-filter-there-is-no-injectable-malformed-record-path-through-the-emitter-s-public-cli-interface-usage-event-state-critique-args-manually-reproduced-the-semantic-difference-directly-against-jq-jq-rc-5-has-signal-empty-on-a-simulated-jq-failure-original-guard-logic-relay-correct-fail-open-mutated-guard-logic-suppress-silently-drops-a-real-record-on-internal-guard-failure-this-is-a-real-disclosed-test-coverage-gap-on-the-fail-open-direction-specifically-not-a-defect-in-the-shipped-guard-manual-repro-confirms-the-shipped-code-is-fail-open-as-designed-and-not-a-failure-of-ac1-ac4-as-written",
      "claimId": "economics-relay-unattributed-suppression-coverage-gap-fail-open-direction-untested.flow-agents-workflow.coverage-gap-not-an-ac-failure-fault-injecting-the-fail-open-guard-itself-reverting-if-jq-rc-eq-0-has-signal-false-to-if-has-signal-true-which-changes-behavior-only-when-the-internal-jq-call-fails-returns-non-true-false-was-not-caught-by-evals-integration-test-economics-record-sh-the-suite-still-reported-all-checks-passed-after-this-mutation-root-cause-the-suite-has-no-black-box-way-to-force-the-guard-s-internal-jq-call-to-fail-because-record-is-always-well-formed-json-assembled-by-the-emitter-s-own-earlier-jq-filter-there-is-no-injectable-malformed-record-path-through-the-emitter-s-public-cli-interface-usage-event-state-critique-args-manually-reproduced-the-semantic-difference-directly-against-jq-jq-rc-5-has-signal-empty-on-a-simulated-jq-failure-original-guard-logic-relay-correct-fail-open-mutated-guard-logic-suppress-silently-drops-a-real-record-on-internal-guard-failure-this-is-a-real-disclosed-test-coverage-gap-on-the-fail-open-direction-specifically-not-a-defect-in-the-shipped-guard-manual-repro-confirms-the-shipped-code-is-fail-open-as-designed-and-not-a-failure-of-ac1-ac4-as-written",
      "evidenceType": "test_output",
      "method": "validation",
      "sourceRef": "economics-relay-unattributed-suppression/evidence.json",
      "excerptOrSummary": "COVERAGE GAP (not an AC failure): fault-injecting the fail-open guard itself (reverting `if [[ $jq_rc -eq 0 && \"$has_signal\" == \"false\" ]]` to `if [[ \"$has_signal\" != \"true\" ]]`, which changes behavior only when the internal jq call fails/returns non-\"true\"/\"false\") was NOT caught by evals/integration/test_economics_record.sh -- the suite still reported all checks passed after this mutation. Root cause: the suite has no black-box way to force the guard's internal jq call to fail, because `$record` is always well-formed JSON assembled by the emitter's own earlier jq filter -- there is no injectable malformed-record path through the emitter's public CLI interface (usage_event/--state/--critique args). Manually reproduced the semantic difference directly against jq (jq_rc=5, has_signal=empty on a simulated jq failure): original guard logic -> RELAY (correct fail-open); mutated guard logic -> SUPPRESS (silently drops a real record on internal guard failure). This is a real, disclosed test-coverage gap on the fail-open direction specifically, not a defect in the shipped guard (manual repro confirms the shipped code is fail-open as designed) and not a failure of AC1-AC4 as written.",
      "observedAt": "2026-07-07T14:41:51Z",
      "collectedBy": "flow-agents/workflow-sidecar",
      "passing": false,
      "execution": {
        "runner": "bash",
        "label": "bash evals/integration/test_economics_record.sh (mutation not caught; manual jq repro confirms semantic difference)",
        "isError": true
      }
    }
